RACE.FOOTNOTES: STAR CANDY had a perfect tracking trip inside watching the contesting pair in the early stages, waited on the fence early in the turn, shifted out three wide at the quarter pole to pounce on the leaders, extended her stride when asked in the four path outside at the furlong marker and was pulling away crossing the finish for the victory. EME CLAIRE took control from the start, set the fractions while hounded outside on the turn, put away the pace rival in upper stretch, could not find more in mid stretch to fend off the closing winner and easily bested the rest at the finish. POPNFIZZ pressed the issue outside down the backside, continued to prompt up front throughout the turn, was in the hunt in the three path turning for home, faded between runners at the furlong marker and finished on the wrong lead to the wire while holding on for the show prize in the end. WITCH HAZEL was last in a tightly bunched field three deep outside at the half mile marker, made little gain on others running three to four wide on the turn, found her best stride late and was gaining on rivals down the stretch settling for a minor share. I HAVE AN IDEA tracked in the two path with runners on either side at the half, was roused to keep position between runners three furlongs from the finish, made little headway on rivals on the turn and could not get involved through the stretch to the finish. I'M INTO MISCHIEF took an awkward step soon after the start, was pulled up quickly and was vanned off back to the barn.

DANCIN IN DA'NILE was mid-pack outside racing mostly four to five wide, had no rally. TAPSASIONAL was bumped at the start, saved ground inside off the pace, was never near enough to threaten.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TOUCH'N RIDE had a good trip watching on the fence the contesting pair in the early stages, rallied up the rail midpoint on the final turn, swung out four wide to bid for the lead in upper stretch, blew on by the pacesetter at the eighth pole and extended his lead comfortably crossing the finish line. OTTAWA took control on the the rail from the onset, was pressed out running down the backstretch, put away the early pace foe at the three furlong pole, was headed outside by the winner in upper stretch, offered no resistance and finished on the wrong lead to the wire holding easily for the place share in the end. LEGAL CATCH tracked the contesting pair outside down the backstretch, was ridden at the three furlong pole, could not catch up to the top pair but did open up on the rest of the field on the far turn and was one paced to the finish holding comfortably in the end for the show money. RAPPER ZAPPER stumbled on the break, settled inside in the third flight down the backside, could not keep up with others on the final turn and found something down the stretch and rallied to the wire for a small share of the prize. COHERENCE broke in at the start, settled near the back of the pack outside, stalked in the third flight outside at the half, offered a brief run through the far turn to be in the mix for a small share at the top of the lane but levelled out on the fence in the last eighth. WHADDYA MEAN hopped at the break trailing inside into the first turn, continued to be unhurried seeing the field down the backside, started to gain some momentum three wide with three eighths to go but could not be a factor running to the finish line. DRYDEN prompted the pace outside in the first turn, hounded the frontrunner outside down the back straight away, could not keep up with rivals when the pace quicken three furlongs from the prize and backed through the field at the quarter marker, was eased crossing the finish line and vanned off

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 13 6 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 80. Maiden Optional Claiming Purse 65900. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD ONTARIO SIRED MAIDENS OR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD MAIDEN CLAIMING PRICE $40,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WHERE IS ESSA was reined back out of the five pronged battle for the front at the half, was pushed out five wide on the turn by inside rival bearing out, gathered himself in the eight path for the stretch run and wore down rivals throughout the lane and got up in deep stretch. SOUPER SUNSHINE broke in brushing the gate at the start, chased the pace down the backside, was bearing out through the turn, angled seven wide for the drive to the wire and closing with determination to be second best at the finish. YODDHA was void of speed trailing down the back straight, advanced smartly on the fence running on the turn, swung four wide for the drive to be in the mix of things and gamely got up between foes to capture third. OLD BLUE CLIFF had a slow start inside, was then hustled on the rail at the five furlong marker to sit behind the pacesetter down the backstretch, chased the frontrunner throughout the turn, bid four wide turning for home, poked his nose in front briefly in mid stretch and stalled in the final sixteenth. LEGS LIKE GIZMO emerged with the lead down the backside after an early five horse tussle for the front in the beginning, opened up mildly on foes on the turn, was collared outside at the top of the lane, fought inside and faded in the last sixteenth. SO CALLED VACATION stalked near the back of the pack between horses the deep at the half, kept pace with others running five wide on the turn, shifted in to the three path for the drive and showed late interest in the final furlong. PREETZAH'S STAR settled near the back five deep down the backstretch, shifted in to save ground trailing the field at the three furlong marker, ran on up the fence at the top of the stretch and passed weary runners down the lane. MIDNIGHT MOONSHINE broke out at the start, was under a snug hold two wide between runners at the half in midfield, put in an early move for position between foes at the three furlong marker to be in the mix up front, gave way by the quarter pole and tired at the furlong marker. GRAND AMBITION stalked near the rear four deep down the back straight, made little impression five wide outside horses on the turn and had nothing to give down the lane. MR. RUDY broke sharp to have a narrow lead at the start, contested four deep up front early, backed through the field midway on the turn and was not a factor in the stretch. ASTAPOVO battled three deep for the front in the early going between foes, lost position between runners at the seven sixteenth marker, was hard ridden midturn, made little headway and stopped in upper stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BONGINO broke in just a bit, had forward position in behind the leaders early, moved to the rail entering the first turn, clipped heels in behind with the following rival, tracked up close inside, found a seam off the inside at the top of the stretch, engaged the leader, dueled with that one, dug in and got the nod. STOLEN MONEY moved forward and shifted in facing outside pressure while setting the pace, dispatched that rival and was in command in upper stretch, engaged by another rival soon after, dueled late and lost the nod. STORMIN DAVE was on the rail heading into the first turn, clipped heels when a rival came over stumbling badly and losing a couple lengths of momentum, regained stride and raced inside up the backstretch, saved ground on the far turn and got show honors. DEFOGGER faced some traffic early heading to the first turn, altered outside a checked rival near the three-quarters, advanced to gain on the leaders but still racing mid-pack two to three wide, came out five wide in upper stretch, missed show. ROOKIE RADAR was forced in just a bit at the start, raced at the back near inside, came out five to six wide turning for home, ran on mildly. BENLION was outpaced in the early going racing toward the back two to three deep, was forced outside foes advancing on the far turn fanning six to seven wide, ran on but needed more. GROOM LAKE stalked three to four wide, was within range to threaten past the quarter pole but faltered in the lane. BAYTOWN ELVIS moved forward with the leader pressing that one from outside, dropped back and faded. BIG RANSOM moved forward willingly after the start, stalked from outside four wide, came up empty. COACH ABERNATHY stumbled at the start, raced outside at the back three to four wide early, continued four to five wide on the far turn, was eased up through the stretch once well beaten, crossed the wire and walked off. FOLLOWING A STEWARDS' INQUIRY AND OBJECTION BY THE RIDER OF STORMIN DAVE AGAINST BONGINO ALLEGING INTERFERENCE, THE LATTER WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM FIRST AND PLACED THIRD BEHIND THE FORMER.
